President Obama has announced that Denis McDonough will be appointed as Assistant to the President and Deputy National Security Advisor. McDonough has been praised for his expertise, work ethic, and collegiality in the field of national security. He has previously served as Chief of Staff of the National Security Staff and Deputy National Security Advisor for Strategic Communications. McDonough has also worked on the Presidential Transition Team and President Obama's 2008 campaign. He has a background in foreign policy and has previously worked in Congress. McDonough is a graduate of St. John's University and Georgetown University. He currently resides in Maryland with his wife and three children.